Selective Open License (SOL)
============================

This software is free and unencumbered, released into the public domain,  
***except for prohibited entities as defined below.***

Anyone, except for the prohibited entities listed in this license,  
is free to copy, modify, publish, use, compile, sell, or distribute  
this software, whether in source code or compiled binary form,  
for any purpose—commercial or non-commercial—by any means,  
as long as such use complies with the principles of fair use.

## Fair Use Restrictions

The use of this software must align with ethical, fair, and responsible practices.  

It must not be used for:
- Any activity that violates laws or infringes on human rights.
- Surveillance, military applications, or systems that compromise privacy.
- Any action that directly or indirectly harms individuals or communities.

## Prohibited Entities

This license explicitly prohibits ***GaonPlatform Corporation, LLC, Inc., or any similar legal entity***  
and its ***subsidiaries, employees, contractors, and affiliates*** from using, 
distributing, or modifying this software in any capacity.  

If you are an ***employee, contractor, or affiliate of any GaonPlatform-related entity***, 
you are ***strictly prohibited*** from using this software in any form or medium.  

## Inquiries & Contributions

Bug reports, feature requests, and pull requests are always welcome.
Please share your feedback through the issue tracker on the project page.

